snippet.textDisplay:
I have two problems with the comments at the end of your video. Your research is incomplete or your word choice is not correct.
1) Western food practices did not create mad cow disease directly. Cows get BSE on their own. It’s a prion disease, lots of species have it. Sheep have a similar disease called Scrapie and humans have one called Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD). Now... western food practices created the Mad Cow OUTBREAK! Yes it did. I’ll agree to that! Lol!!
2) Western meat consumption isn’t the sole contributing factor to antibiotic resistance. I work in the veterinary industry and it’s a big battle between the animal world and the human world as to who is responsible for creating the antibiotic resistant bugs.
Both sides are 100% to blame. The human heath industry hands out antibiotics to everything (even when people don’t need them (cuz clients are uneducated)), plus they don’t use the correct antibiotic. THANKFULLY that’s changing with the “not all bugs need drugs” ads, and I’ve had the pharmacist question the doctors choice in antibiotics for a cat bite vs a cat scratch. So changes are happening. (I don’t work with food production animals, but I know in small animals, we are working on not handing out antibiotics if we don’t need to.)
